criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  consenting adult Caucasian men and women, aged ≤65 y;

          -  a seated office systolic BP >120 and <160 mmHg and/or a diastolic BP >80 and <95 mmHg
             (based on the mean BP across 3 screening visits as part of a pre-intervention phase of
             the trial)

          -  willing to consume study breads

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  taking anti-hypertensive medication;

          -  taking any medications known to interfere with blood pressure or calcium or bone
             metabolism;

          -  Severe medical illness;

          -  celiac disease;

          -  hypercalcemia;

          -  known intestinal malabsorption syndrome,

          -  excessive alcohol use (>14 drinks/week);

          -  pregnancy
